The classification of graphic arts. The structure of art teaching. Dealing with different techniques and their methodology. Depicting and designing. Encouraging imagination. Vertical and horizontal trends.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce art as a subject, its structure, syllabus, important techniques and methods of depicting and designing animate and inanimate nature.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course:
- knows the structure of the Art Studies;
- applies all the materials, resources, techniques mentioned in the syllabus and uses speciality related terminology his/her creative work as well as his/her work as a teacher;
- evaluates creative work from the different aspects, expression and inclinations.
